[{"location":"reference/#Reference","page":"Reference","title":"Reference","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"reference/#TwistedBoundaryConditions.TwistedBoundaryConditions","page":"Reference","title":"TwistedBoundaryConditions.TwistedBoundaryConditions","text":"Optimal twisted boundary conditions for exact diagonalization of quantum many-body systems.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"module"},{"location":"reference/#TwistedBoundaryConditions.calculate_optimal_tbc-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{Int64, AbstractVector{<:AbstractVector{T}}}} where T<:Real","page":"Reference","title":"TwistedBoundaryConditions.calculate_optimal_tbc","text":"calculate_optimal_tbc(Ns::Int, basis_vectors::Vector{Vector{T}}; search_range::Int=3) where {T<:Real}\n\nGeneralized optimal TBC calculator for arbitrary dimension D.\n\nArguments\n\nNs: Total number of sites.\nbasis_vectors: List of D basis vectors (e.g., [[1.0, 0.0], [-0.5, 0.866]]).\nsearch_range: Range for integers in the twist matrix.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#TwistedBoundaryConditions.generate_unimodular_matrices-Tuple{Int64, Int64}","page":"Reference","title":"TwistedBoundaryConditions.generate_unimodular_matrices","text":"generate_unimodular_matrices(dim::Int, limit::Int)\n\nGenerates DxD integer matrices with determinant 1. Entries are within range [-limit, limit]. WARNING: The number of matrices grows as (2*limit+1)^(D^2). Keep limit small (1 or 2).\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#TwistedBoundaryConditions.get_factors_recursive-Tuple{Int64, Int64}","page":"Reference","title":"TwistedBoundaryConditions.get_factors_recursive","text":"get_factors_recursive(Ns, dim)\n\nRecursively finds all factorizations of Ns into dim integers. Returns a list of vectors, e.g., [[2, 2, 3], [1, 4, 3], ...] for Ns=12, dim=3.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#TwistedBoundaryConditions.lll_reduction-Union{Tuple{AbstractVector{<:AbstractVector{T}}}, Tuple{T}} where T<:Real","page":"Reference","title":"TwistedBoundaryConditions.lll_reduction","text":"lll_reduction(basis::Vector{Vector{T}}; delta=0.75) where {T<:Real}\n\nPerforms LLL lattice reduction to find a basis with short, nearly orthogonal vectors. Essential for defining a meaningful aspect ratio in D > 2.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"index/#Index","page":"Index","title":"Index","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#TwistedBoundaryConditions.jl","page":"Home","title":"TwistedBoundaryConditions.jl","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#Installation","page":"Home","title":"Installation","text":"The package is not yet registered in the Julia general registry. It can be installed trough the package manager with the following command:\n\npkg> add git@github.com:ManyBodyLab/TwistedBoundaryConditions.jl.git","category":"section"},{"location":"#Code-Samples","page":"Home","title":"Code Samples","text":"# --- Usage Example (3D) ---\n# Simple Cubic Basis\njulia> using TwistedBoundaryConditions\njulia> b1 = [1.0, 0.0, 0.0]; b2 = [0.0, 1.0, 0.0]; b3 = [0.0, 0.0, 1.0];\njulia> Ns, U, ratio = calculate_optimal_tbc(12, [b1, b2, b3], search_range=1);\njulia> println(\"Optimal Ns: $Ns\")\nOptimal Ns: [1, 3, 4]\njulia> println(\"Optimal U matrix: \\n$U\")\nOptimal U matrix:\n[0 -1 -1; -1 0 -1; 1 -1 -1]\njulia> println(\"Aspect Ratio: $ratio\")\nAspect Ratio: 0.8164965809277259\n# Triangular Lattice Basis\njulia> b2 = [1.0, 0.0]; b1 = [-0.5, sqrt(3)/2]\njulia> Ns, U, ratio = calculate_optimal_tbc(21, [b1, b2], search_range=1)\njulia> println(\"Optimal Ns: $Ns\")\nOptimal Ns: [3, 7]\njulia> println(\"Optimal U matrix: \\n$U\")\nOptimal U matrix:\n[0 -1; 1 -1]\njulia> println(\"Aspect Ratio: $ratio\")\nAspect Ratio: 0.6735753140545634\njulia> b2 = [1.0, 0.0]; b1 = [-0.5, sqrt(3)/2]\njulia> Ns, U, ratio = calculate_optimal_tbc(21, [b1, b2], search_range=2)\njulia> println(\"Optimal Ns: $Ns\")\nOptimal Ns: [3, 7]\njulia> println(\"Optimal U matrix: \\n$U\")\nOptimal U matrix:\n[1 -2; 1 -1]\njulia> println(\"Aspect Ratio: $ratio\")\nAspect Ratio: 0.9571859726038531","category":"section"},{"location":"#License","page":"Home","title":"License","text":"TwistedBoundaryConditions.jl is licensed under the MIT License). By using or interacting with this software in any way, you agree to the license of this software.\n\n\n\nThis page was generated using Literate.jl.","category":"section"}]
